    <statement>
        
        
                <p>
                    Kurbika's Bridge Club is choosing among 13 unique prizes for their upcoming tournament. If each of the first 7 places will receive a prize, how many possible ways can the prizes be handed out?
                </p> 
        
        <p>

        </p>
        <p>
        Show all of your steps, specify which formula you used, and state why you used it.
        </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <p> We are selecting 7 from a total of 13 possibilities (without repeats), and the order of the selections matters. There are <m>_{13}P_{7}</m> <m> = 8648640</m> possibilities.</p>
    </answer>
</exercise>
